Hunts

Hunt down and defeat marks to claim bounties!
Access the Hunts page by tapping the Hunts button on the World Map.

A permit is required to go on a hunt. Use your available permits to undertake a hunt, defeat the mark, and earn your deserved reward!

*Note that it is not possible to call on friends for support for daily hunts.
Daily Hunt Marks
Daily hunt marks that are currently available will be advertised on the Hunts page.
Be sure to stay sharp, as marks may be added or changed on a regular basis.
Permits
Hunting marks requires permits. You can confirm the number of daily hunt permits in your possession on the Hunts page.

One permit will be issued to you daily at 08:00 UTC, and you may carry up to three permits at once.

A permit will not be consumed until the mark is defeated, so don't give up if you fail to bring it down on the first try!

Daily Hunt Co-op
You may also invite or join your friends for daily hunt quests.
A daily hunt permit is required to host a hunt co-op, and guests may choose to use their permits as well to also obtain Hunt Rewards for defeating the hunt mark!

Elite Hunts
Elite hunts are dangerous hunts which can only be undertaken solo.
Before you can embark on an elite hunt, you will need to exchange Dissidia Points for an elite hunt application in the DP Exchange. You can exchange for a maximum of one elite hunt application per week.

Upon exchanging for the elite hunt application, you will obtain an elite hunt permit featuring a random hunt mark. The corresponding mark will then be added to the Hunts page.
An elite hunt permit is only valid for a period of one week following obtainment, so make sure to take down the mark by then!
Token Exchange
The dailies tokens rewarded for defeating marks may be exchanged for items in the dailies token exchange.

Seasonal Hunts
Occasionally, you might be able to take on seasonal hunts!
These hunts may use different systems from the daily hunt, so refer to their respective notices for more details.
